<p> Military Time </p>\
<p> Military time is a standardized timekeeping system used by the military, emergency services, and other organizations around the world. Rather than using a 12-hour standard clock with AM and PM designations, military time uses a <em>24-hour clock</em> system. </p>\
<p> In military time, each hour of the day is represented by a unique four-digit number. The first two digits represent the hour, and the second two digits represent the minutes. Therefore, 1600 military time is the way of expressing 4:00 PM in military format. </p>\
<p> This system is commonly used in military, aviation, emergency services, and other contexts where clarity and precision in timekeeping are critical. It eliminates confusion over AM and PM and simplifies calculations involving time intervals. </p>\
<p> A watch system, watch schedule, or watch bill is a method of assigning regular periods of work duty aboard ships and some other areas of employment. A watch system allows the ship's crew to effectively operate the ship 24 hours a day for the duration of long voyages or operations. </p>\
